originalText.text: Ate here for my birthday and had a top notch experience from beginning to end. We ordered most of the menu and loved every bite! The yams are by far the best appetizer, and I loved the steak and branzino too! I recommend the rum & ting cocktail. They make the drinks strong! The server even brought out a birthday candle in our dessert! Will definitely be going back. I am so happy to have this gem of a restaurant in the neighborhood.

originalText.text: Im so impressed with this place, I wish I could give it more stars! Neatly tucked on Park ave, this is truly a gem of East Harlem. Delicious food, awesome music and a lovely staff. Immediately when I walked in, I was surprised by the vibe. I love the menu options. I had the pancakes which came with candied plantains, the plantains were a bit too hard for me to chew but the pancakes were fluffy and made to perfection. My only gripe was there were no lattes nor cappuccino. This felt like a place that should have that but they do serve an assortment of teas. The jerk chicken sausage was soo good. We ordered two of those. Overall this place gets 10/10! I would definitely come back and I highly recommend anyone come here and see for themselves.

originalText.text: Absolutely loved my experience here. Made a last minute reservation for dinner for 9:30 PM. The kitchen is open until 10:30. The decor is warm, cozy, and inviting. The food was delicious! I had the branzino which was tender and flaky, well seasoned with a really flavorful sauce. My date had the coconut fish sandwich which he ravaged. We also got the sauteed collard greens which werenâ€™t too salty and quite fresh. The curried carrots were also delicious, a perfect mix of spices and a little sweetness. We finished with the cheesecake and the crust was so buttery, I could have eaten that alone. Finally the service was immaculate. Every person greeted us, they were attentive and kind. They joked with us and shared a bit about their background. They were knowledgeable about the menu and able to answer questions. Everything was so good, weâ€™ll be back!

originalText.text: This was a place a friend of my recommended and I was excited to support a neighborhood established. The food was delicious and the cocktails were top tier. I was taken back a little by the portions of some of the dishes in correlation to their price. However, the vibe, the flavor and the music made everything worth while. I highly recommend for an intimate gathering or date night.
